Question: what are the key things you would consider when creating/consuming an API to ensure that it is secure and reliable?

Answer: 
There are some things that we need to follow which are as follows.

Authentication: We need to provide some authentication while building API like this. To secure our data as we are using open
API to get all the data.

Authorization: Also we need to check weather the user is authorized or not.

Encryption: We need to encrypt some important data such as password while persisting it in database.

Validation: We have to provide some validation to our entity objects to avoid unnecessary load/transaction to database.

Exception: We need to create some user defined exceptions so that we can send proper message to the user/client after getting an error. 

Structure: We have to some structure while building an API so that anyone can understand our code.